Chicken tikka masala was so creamy and delicious. The naan is also amazing. My favorite Indian food in Ithaca by far.

I had Shahi Pakwan for the first time tonight. I love Indian food and the Matar Mushroom dish I had was extremely delicious. The rice is very light but hearty. I had a sweet Lassi for dessert and it was the perfect meal. Highly recommended!
They make dosas! The filling was very tasty, included chutneys and mild sambar/vegetable soup, and our vegetable korma had great spice and flavor. We will come again.
Best local spot for Indian! Actually spicy if you ask for it. Solid Naan as well

I ordered veggie samosas, garlic nan, and lamb vindaloo. The samosas were very tasty and perfectly prepared. The garlic nan was garlicky and delicious. The lamb vindaloo had a bright, vibrant flavor. I also loved the pickles. It was my first time and I’ll definitely be back for more.
Very good authentic Indian Food I love it.

Best Indian food in Ithaca as far as I'm concerned. I've been happy every time I've been there. It's my go to take out spot. Strong recommend for the Sag Mushroom and samosas!

This place is very good , better then all the other Indian restaurants in Ithaca in my opinion , They’re friendly  and the place is clean

This restaurant just opened recently. It complements the other Indian options available in Ithaca. It is convenient and has a buffet for lunch. The owner is really friendly and happy to customize orders to suit your tastes and needs. It is hard to see from the street but worth looking for.

Best Indian food I have had in Ithaca! The food was flavorful, perfectly spiced, and authentic. Will come back for sure!

Wonderfully delicious food, warm and attentive service. They were able to adjust dishes to allergies and preferences in our party. Everything was so good, I went back the next day! You should do the same!

Just finished my meal. Fantastic food. Get the bread basket. Has every kind of naan you could want. Best dosa in Ithaca. Prices best bargain for Indian food in Ithaca.

Best Indian food for the money in Ithaca. ~$30 for an appetizer, 2 garlic naans, and 2 entrees. Food is great and the owners are very nice. Always feel welcome there.

Best Indian food in Ithaca by far and my new favorite lunch spot.  Fresh and delicious food. The owners are friendly, the place is very clean, and the selection is fantastic. I work a block from a competitor, and choose to go much farther for the superior selection and flavor.

Really friendly staff and delicious naan bread. The lunch buffet is a real steal and the selection is fantastic. Shahi Pakwan is definitely worth giving a try over the other options in Collegetown and The Commons.
